JOHANNESBURG DJ Zinhle's fraud accused boyfriend, Brendon Naidoo was granted R50,000 bail on Tuesday by the Alexandra Magistrate s Court.State prosecutor Jimmy Shongwe told the court that Naidoo allegedly committed fraud through forex exchange transactions valued at R1,2-million. Naidoo is facing charges theft and fraud, which are schedule five offences.Shongwe had asked the court to set Naidoo s bail at R100,000, but his lawyer, Jay Naidoo, successfully argued for half the amount which he said was reasonable and reachable .The defence said the accused could only afford R50,000 and would be able to report to the Sandton police station on Monday and Friday.Naidoo became famous after posing on social media with with DJ Zinhle, whose real name is Ntombezinhle Jiyane. In a romantic post DJ Zinhle referred to the accused as Bond . "Whenever you focus on the blessings in your life, you're instantaneously on the blessings frequency and blessings increase in your life in that moment. I'm truly blessed every day by every person and every circumstance. How are you blessed?" #Alive #Grateful #BlessedA post shared by Brendon (@brendonnaidoo) on Naidoo splashes pictures of his lavish lifestyle on his Instagram. In some pictures he is being chauffeur-driven in expensive vehicles. There are also video clips of him overseas in posh penthouses.The accused has been in a relationship with the DJ for nearly a year, following her highly publicised split from rapper Kienan AKA Forbes, the father of her daughter.Naidoo is expected back in court on May 5. African News Agency